The paper discusses methods for constructing feature vectors for molecular shape recognition, which is a problem in machine learning and computer vision (cs.LG, cs.CV). The use of spherical harmonics and principal component analysis suggests a mathematical and statistical approach, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and computational engineering (cs.CE). The discussion of lossy compression also suggests a focus on data storage and retrieval, which falls under the category of databases (cs.DB).
